data.enText: to make a short low sound in the throat
to make a short low sound in your throat, especially to show that you are in pain, annoyed or not interested; to say sth using this sound

data.chText: 他边用力边哼声，使出更大的力气拉绳子。
data.enText: He pulled harder on the rope, grunting with the effort.

data.chText: 我告诉她出了什么事，她只哼了一声就又看起书来了。
data.enText: When I told her what had happened she just grunted and turned back to her book.

data.chText: 他嘟哝着说要迟到了便匆匆跑了出去。
data.enText: He grunted something about being late and rushed out.

data.chText: 哼声；咕哝声；嘟哝声；（尤指猪的）呼噜声
data.enText: a short, low sound made by a person or an animal (especially a pig)

data.chText: 发出费力 / 痛苦的哼声
data.enText: to give a grunt of effort/pain

data.chText: 工作乏味收入低的工人
data.enText: a worker who does boring tasks for low pay

word_means: 工作乏味收入低的工人

means: 工作乏味收入低的工人

tr: medium-sized tropical marine food fishes that utter grunting sounds when caught
the short low gruff noise of the kind made by hogs
an unskilled or low-ranking soldier or other worker
example: infantrymen in Vietnam were called grunts
he went from grunt to chairman in six years

tr: issue a grunting, low, animal-like noise

value.def: If you grunt, you make a low sound, especially because you are annoyed or not interested in something.

example.ex: The driver grunted, convinced that Michael was crazy...
example.tran: 司机嘟哝了一声，认定迈克尔是发疯了。

example.ex: Their replies were no more than grunts of acknowledgement.
example.tran: 他们所谓的回答不过是表示承认的咕哝罢了。

value.tran: （尤指因为烦恼或不感兴趣）咕噜，嘟哝着说

value.def: When an animal grunts, it makes a low rough noise.
